<refnamediv>
<refname>miktex-xetex</refname>
<refpurpose>Unicode-based &TeX; engine</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>

<cmdsynopsis>
&miktexxetex;
<arg choice="opt" rep="repeat"><replaceable>option</replaceable></arg>
<group>
<arg choice="opt"><replaceable>file</replaceable></arg>
<arg choice="opt" rep="repeat">\<replaceable>command</replaceable></arg>
</group></cmdsynopsis>

</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1>

<title>Description</title>

<para>Run the &XeTeX; typesetter on <replaceable>file</replaceable>,
usually creating <filename>file.pdf</filename>. If the file argument
has no extension, <filename>.tex</filename> will be appended to
it. Instead of a file name, a set of &XeTeX; commands can be given,
the first of which must start with a backslash.</para>

<para>&XeTeX; has simple font installation;
it can use any installed fonts in the operating system
without configuring &TeX; font metric. As a result, &XeTeX;
can access font features such as special ligatures and variable
font weights.</para>

</refsect1>

